<p><a href="https://www.xsede.org/-/xsede-joins-hpc-consortium-for-covid-19-research"><span style="font-weight: 400;">XSEDE joins HPC Consortium for COVID-19 Research</span></a><br /><span style="font-weight: 400;">XSEDE and the XSEDE Resource Allocations System (</span><a href="https://portal.xsede.org/allocations/about-xras"><span style="font-weight: 400;">XRAS</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">) are proud to be contributing to the newly-announced COVID-19 HPC Consortium, a private/government/academic partnership. Researchers who are interested in conducting this timely work are asked to </span><a href="https://www.xsede.org/covid19-hpc-consortium"><span style="font-weight: 400;">submit research proposals to the COVID-19 Online Portal here</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, which is handled by the XRAS team.</span></p>
<p><a href="https://coronavirus.frontiersin.org/iuis-collaboration"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Coronavirus Research Collaboration<br />T</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">he</span><a href="https://iuis.org/webinars/"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> International Union of Immunological Societies (IUIS)</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is collaborating with Frontiers to accelerate the development of novel diagnostics, therapeutics and vaccines against coronavirus.</span></p>
<p><a href="https://www.feinberg.northwestern.edu/sites/cch/docs/staying-engaged-during-covid-19f2.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Community Engagement Resources</span></a><br /><span style="font-weight: 400;">We encourage researchers who are planning or currently conducting community-engaged research studies to review the resources developed by ARCC regarding community partnerships during the COVID-19 pandemic.</span></p>
<p><a href="https://www.samhsa.gov/sites/default/files/training-and-technical-assistance-covid19.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Training and Technical Assistance Related to COVID-19</span></a><br /><span style="font-weight: 400;">SAMHSA is committed to providing regular training and technical assistance (TTA) on matters related to the mental and substance use disorder field as they deal with COVID-19.</span></p>
<p><a href="https://www.aascu.org/grc/grantweekweb.aspx?id=11775&amp;pubdate=2020-04-06#15"><span style="font-weight: 400;">National Academies to Host Forums on the Postsecondary Response to COVID-19</span></a><br /><span style="font-weight: 400;">The National Academies of Sciences, Engineering, and Medicine (</span><a href="https://www.nationalacademies.org/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">NASEM</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">) is hosting a series of virtual events this month to bring together academic, industry, government, and civic leaders across the country to explore the current and future impact of the COVID-19 (coronavirus) epidemic and help shape the response from researchers and academia in the weeks and months ahead.&nbsp; ​</span></p>
<p><a href="https://www.aascu.org/grc/grantweekweb.aspx?id=11775&amp;pubdate=2020-04-06#20"><span style="font-weight: 400;">COVID-19 Update: SSTI Compiles Resources Related to Economic Development</span></a><br /><span style="font-weight: 400;">The State Science &amp; Technology Institute (SSTI) has added its own compendium of resources to the growing number of resource hubs related to the federal government&rsquo;s response to the COVID-19 (coronavirus) epidemic. In keeping with its mission, SSTI&rsquo;s website compiles links to new federal guidelines and announcements in response to COVID-19 with the potential to affect initiatives at the intersection of regional economic development, scientific research and innovation, and entrepreneurship.</span></p>
<p><a href="https://www.biospace.com/article/releases/novartis-and-the-novartis-us-foundation-establish-usd-5-million-us-covid-19-community-response-fund/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Novartis and the Novartis US Foundation establish USD 5 million US COVID-19 Community Response Fund</span></a><br /><span style="font-weight: 400;">On April 3, <a href="https://www.biospace.com/employer/551985/novartis/">Novartis</a> announced that in response to the COVID-19 pandemic in the US, Novartis and the Novartis US Foundation have established a US COVID-19 Community Response Fund. The Fund will provide cash and in-kind donations totalling USD 5 million for immediate response and recovery efforts related to the pandemic.To apply to the Novartis US COVID-19 Community Response Fund, please visit novartis.us/coronavirus.</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></table><!-- ELEMENT_1603154_STOP --><!--CONTENT_ENDS--> 
